first)\n**So that** the most critical patients are seen first\n\n### Details and Assumptions\n* Urgency level is 
represented by a numeric value where lower numbers indicate higher urgency.\n* Arrival time is recorded as a 
timestamp.\n* Sorting applies to the entire patient queue.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n```gherkin\nGiven the 
patient queue contains multiple patients with different urgency levels and arrival times\nWhen the queue is 
sorted\nThen patients are ordered by urgency level ascending (lowest number first)\nAnd for patients with the same
urgency level, they are ordered by arrival time ascending (earliest first)\n```', 10: '**As a** triage nurse\n**I 
