  final_answer("""                                                                                                
  ### 1. Task outcome (short version):                                                                            
  Successfully built and verified a complete triage queue management frontend (Vite + React + TypeScript) that    
  covers all 6 user stories, connects to the real backend via axios, passes static analysis checks, builds        
  successfully, and passes all 4 tests.                                                                           
                                                                                                                  
  ### 2. Task outcome (extremely detailed version):                                                               
                                                                                                                  
  **Feature groups implemented and pages created:**                                                               
                                                                                                                  
  | User Story | Page/Component | Implementation |                                                                
  |---|---|---|                                                                                                   
  | 1. Patient Registration with Symptoms | `RegisterPage.tsx` | Form with symptoms textarea + urgency dropdown,  
  calls `POST /api/v1/patients` |                                                                                 
  | 2. Urgency Level Assignment (1-5) | `RegisterPage.tsx` | 5-level dropdown (Critical→Minimal), maps to         
  urgencyLevel 1-5 |                                                                                              
  | 3. Queue Sorting by Urgency and Time | `QueuePage.tsx` | Fetches patients via `GET /api/v1/patients`, sorts   
  by urgencyLevel asc then arrivalTime asc |                                                                      
  | 4. Queue Reordering on New Patient or Re-triage | `QueuePage.tsx` | Re-triage button calls `PUT               
  /api/v1/patients/{id}`, refreshes sorted queue |                                                                
  | 5. Physician Takes Next Patient | `QueuePage.tsx` | 'Take Patient' button calls `DELETE                       
  /api/v1/patients/{id}`, removes from queue |                                                                    
  | 6. Live Dashboard with Urgency and Wait Time | `DashboardPage.tsx` | Fetches via `GET                         
  /api/v1/patients/dashboard`, auto-refreshes every 30s |                                                         
                                                                                                                  
  **API endpoints covered:**                                                                                      
  - `GET /api/v1/patients` — listPatients                                                                         
  - `GET /api/v1/patients/dashboard` — getDashboard                                                               
  - `POST /api/v1/patients` — createPatient                                                                       
  - `PUT /api/v1/patients/{id}` — updatePatient                                                                   
